overview: The user initiated a request to fix a pull request riddled with
  issues, including critical security flaws and broken Vercel deploys. The
  assistant began by thoroughly analyzing the PR comments and CI failures,
  identifying a range of problems from a trivially forgeable admin
  authentication cookie to various bugs in PDF generation and API validation. A
  key discovery was that some lint errors reported by CI were already fixed
  locally but not committed. The assistant systematically addressed each issue,
  prioritizing the critical security vulnerability by implementing an existing
  HMAC-based session system. Other fixes included adding input validation for
  API parameters, introducing pagination for CSV exports, correcting PDF
  calculation logic to handle empty inputs and include minutes, enabling the PDF
  download button, and enhancing time field validation in the Zod schema. After
  all fixes, the code passed lint and TypeScript checks, and the relevant
  changes were staged for commit.
